# {{product_name_pascal}}

> Hybrid monorepo scaffolded by [Ulak OS](https://github.com/osrt91/ulak-os). Single-repo, multi-service stack with shared types + UI + config.

## Structure

```
{{product_name}}/
├── apps/
│   ├── web/         # Next.js 16 — customer/admin/partner surfaces
│   ├── api/         # FastAPI 0.115+ — business logic + heavy compute
│   ├── mobile/      # Expo SDK 52+ — iOS + Android app
│   └── bot/         # aiogram 3.x — Telegram bot
├── packages/
│   ├── shared/      # types + Zod schemas + constants (consumed by web + mobile)
│   ├── ui/          # RN + web shared components (nativewind)
│   └── config/      # tsconfig presets + eslint + tailwind + prettier
├── infrastructure/
│   ├── docker-compose.yml      # dev stack
│   ├── docker-compose.prod.yml # prod overrides
│   ├── traefik/                # edge proxy
│   └── acme.json.sh            # Let's Encrypt bootstrap
├── scripts/
├── CLAUDE.md                    # Ulak OS governance entry
├── pnpm-workspace.yaml
├── turbo.json
└── package.json
```

## Getting started

```bash
# Install all workspace deps
pnpm install

# Start every service in parallel (watch mode)
pnpm dev

# Or start one at a time
pnpm dev:web
pnpm dev:api
pnpm dev:mobile   # launches Expo dev server
pnpm dev:bot      # polls Telegram

# Full-stack dev with docker-compose (postgres + redis + mailhog)
pnpm compose:up

# Production-parity stack (Traefik + Let's Encrypt)
pnpm compose:prod
```

## Shared packages

Every app can import from shared packages via `workspace:*`:

```ts
// apps/web/app/(customer)/dashboard/page.tsx
import type { UserProfile } from "@{{product_name}}/shared";
import { Button } from "@{{product_name}}/ui";

// apps/mobile/app/(tabs)/profile.tsx
import type { UserProfile } from "@{{product_name}}/shared";
import { Avatar } from "@{{product_name}}/ui";
```

Changes to `packages/*` auto-rebuild during `pnpm dev` via Turborepo's dependency graph.

## Governance

This repo was scaffolded with Ulak OS governance pre-wired. See:

- `CLAUDE.md` — imports Ulak OS core contract + runtime rules
- `.claude/settings.json` — permission allowlist (hardened per SEC-B-04, v1.0.0)
- `docs/runtime/anti-patterns.md` — Ulak OS anti-pattern catalog (applies to every app)

Run `/director komple` in Claude Code to audit the current state. Run `/pack-gap-audit` to see which additional Ulak packs you should activate for your domain.

## Deploy

- Dev: `pnpm compose:up` (localhost)
- Staging: `pnpm compose:prod` on a single VPS with Traefik + Let's Encrypt
- Production: multi-VPS via `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` (webhook-triggered; signed payload)

See `infrastructure/README.md` for the full topology.

